<td style=" color:#000000; font-size:12pt; background-color:#FFFFFF; font-family:arial; bLabel:main; bEditID:r3st1;" tEditID="c1r1" locked="0" aEditID="c1r1" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" size="6" color="#000066">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="4" color="#ff6600"><i>Chartered By The British Schools Foundation</i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="6" color="#c0c0c0"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="1" color="#ff6600"><i><br></i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><div style="font-family: Times; font-size: medium;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">7th November 2014</font></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 5px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 5px; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation}&nbsp;{!Contact.FirstName}&nbsp;{!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><br></div><div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">The appointments for the IGCSE Science teachers are full and I understand that a number of parents are trying to make appointments beyond the given times. Biology, Chemistry and Physics together comprise the full Science Double and Triple Awards IGCSEs. Science is a valuable core subject and it is important that you are able to meet with the Science teachers.</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">In order that every parent has the opportunity to discuss their son/daughter's progress in Science IGCSE, we will restructure the appointment schedule. This means that every parent will be given an appointment to meet with one of the Science teachers who will consult with you about academic progress across all three elements (Biology, Chemistry and Physics) of the IGCSE. Science teachers will meet beforehand to coordinate progress comments so that all teachers will be able to feed back on individual sciences.</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">The Science Department will consult with students today to create a new appointment schedule. We will aim to keep as close as possible to the original requested times so as to minimise inconvenience. The new appointment schedule will be reissued as soon as possible. If there is a particular issue with an individual science subject, we will address this using available time during the evening or as soon as possible afterwards.</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">We appreciate that this could affect on other subject times. However, other subjects are not over-subscribed and have flexibility within their appointment times.</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">I thank you for your understanding for making the changes, but it now means that every parent has the opportunity to meet a Science teacher to discuss progress in IGCSE Science.</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">If you have any queries, please contact me or Miss Burton-Morgan.</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">jason.reeves@britishschool.edu.my</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">jasmin.burtonmorgan@britishschool.edu.my</font></div><div><br></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Yours faithfully,</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Jason Reeves</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Head of Pupil Development and Geography Teacher</font></div></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><i><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600"><b>World Class Education</b></font></i></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">__________________________________________________________</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">{!User.School_List_Email_Footer__c}</font><font class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">&nbsp;</font></div>]]></td>
